    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Parallelizable, Panicable, Step<org.eclipse.collections.api.iterator.LongIterator>
    public class ReadRecordsStep<RECORD extends AbstractBaseRecord>
extends ProcessorStep<org.eclipse.collections.api.iterator.LongIterator>
    Reads records from a RecordStore and sends batches of those records downstream. A PageCursor is used during the life cycle of this Step, e.g. between start(int) and ProcessorStep.close().

      • process

        protected void process​(org.eclipse.collections.api.iterator.LongIterator idRange,
                       BatchSender sender,
                       PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        Description copied from class: ProcessorStep
        Processes a received batch. Any batch that should be sent downstream as part of processing the supplied batch should be done so using BatchSender.send(Object). The most typical implementation of this method is to process the received batch, either by creating a new batch object containing some derivative of the received batch, or the batch object itself with some modifications and emit that in the end of the method.
        Specified by:
        process in class ProcessorStep<org.eclipse.collections.api.iterator.LongIterator>
        Parameters:
        idRange - batch to process.
        sender - BatchSender for sending zero or more batches downstream.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer
